)clear all

-- Work with polynomials over the rationals
-- Groebner basis of a small ideal in Q[x, y]
-- Example system: { x*y - 1, x^2 - y }
-- The Groebner basis under lex order (typically) reveals elimination structure.

F := [x*y - 1, x^2 - y]
lexGroebner(F, [x, y])$PolyGroebner(Integer)

-- Another example: circle and line intersection ideal
G := [x^2 + y^2 - 1, y - x]
lexGroebner(G, [x, y])$PolyGroebner(Integer)

-- Change variable order by changing the symbol list:
lexGroebner(G, [y, x])$PolyGroebner(Integer)
-- (For degree-based order, try: totalGroebner(G, [x, y])$PolyGroebner(Integer))


